                                                                                                            Soros buys 3% of Anil firm
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, Feb. 7: Renowned American investor George Soros has acquired a 3 per cent stake in Anil Ambanis Reliance Entertainment.        
	According to investment bankers, Soros has paid $100 million, effectively valuing the company at $3 billion.        
	Soros is among a group of investors who earlier invested $14 billion in another Reliance ADAG company, Reliance Telecom Infrastructure Ltd, which owns transmission towers and the infrastructure of Reliance Communications.         
	The Hungarian-born stock investor, having a net worth of $8.5 billion, believes India is currently the flavour of the world and has large investments in the country, especially in the real estate, infrastructure and financial services sectors. Officials in Reliance Entertainment confirmed the news but did not elaborate on how the company planned to spend the money raised.        
	Reliance Entertainment is spearheading Reliance ADAGs foray into media and entertainment.                                                                                                                                        
